This directory references the ODIR-5K (Ocular Disease Intelligent Recognition)
dataset for the venth `retina-screening` demo example.

Source:  https://www.kaggle.com/datasets/andrewmvd/ocular-disease-recognition-odir5k
License: CC BY 4.0 (https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0/)
Cite:    ODIR-5K: Ocular Disease Intelligent Recognition. Kaggle,
         andrewmvd/ocular-disease-recognition-odir5k.

What is bundled here:
  data/full_df.csv          per-patient labels & metadata (~1.5 MB), redistributed
                            unmodified. The columns `dr_referable` (from `D`),
                            `patient_sex` and `patient_age` are derived for the
                            fairness/sensitivity evaluation; see
                            data/odir.croissant.json for the field-level provenance.

What is NOT bundled (size, not licence — ~2 GB):
  the fundus images. The pipeline reads them from `$SEI_ODIR_CACHE/preprocessed_images/`
  at build time. Re-runners fetch the CC BY 4.0 images from the Kaggle source above.
